,Not Recommended,224920,20478844,"Posted: 11 January, 2016",all,RadioSwim,"Is it a bad game? No, it's actually quite good, easily one of the best games to come out of the PlayStation's catalog.Do I recommend it? Absolutel not. If you still have a PS1 laying around, find an old copy of that version instead.Why? Controller support. It's abbysmal. It barely supports enough of the buttons from the Xbox controller base drivers. In order for it to be barely playable, I had to fidget with the drivers to assign keys regularly used, to keys that were not. In order for the camera to usable, I had to assign two shoulder buttons to the start/select button, as for some reason those are the default camera buttons? WHAT? Not to mention they're the only open keys that you have left after assigning all the other gameplay actions to your buttons [action, jump, aim, etc]Even after all this, good luck using the joysticks to aim, or move. The game doesn't support incremental input from joysticks, so if you move that thing barely when aiming or moving and it goes FULL BORE! PLATFORMING YAY!!! PRECISE AIMING YAY!!!!Until the controller support is expanded, and refined, I'd give the PC version of this a pass.(Unless ofcourse someone has modded it already? I haven't found anything about it)"
