,Recommended,224920,25110663,"Posted: 24 August, 2016",all,bread,"This game is great, it's a gem from a time when none of my friend's PC had the power to actually play it.  To me it was a darker version Ocarina of Time, with a relatively open world and a progressive set of abilities/equipment to help you unlock the paths throughout the world.  There is even a somewhat Link to the Past themed light/dark world mechanic at play, where you manifest in the physical and spirit worlds to solve puzzles.  And the puzzles are rewarding, mostly revolving around moving blocks around a 3D space, sometimes requiring proper orientation or stacking/destacking of blocks to add more challenge.Unfortunately the PC version (not sure if only Steam's) has an issue with the sound that begins to loop sound effects after playing for a while, so I would recommend purchasing this for the legal ownership and then emulating the Playstation version that doesn't seem to have this glitch.  Of course there is a graphics patch for the PC version so if muting the sound or just ignoring the out of place sounds doesn't bother you..TL:DR This game is worth your money and time, even in 2016."
