,Recommended,224920,32593750,Posted: 20 June,all,Crash,"I'm not entirely sure if I should really recommend this game... read on to understand.This is a PSX game that was ported to PC in 1999, and therefore there are a lot of problems in running old PC games in windows 10. This game is locked into fullscreen, does not support ximput controllers (unless you use software mapping for directimput) and does not support a lot of resolutions as well. There are also sound problems, like sfx and music just stopping from time to time.But the patch made by the user Wrace fixes most of these stuff. Still, there's a high chance the game just crash when alt-tabbing (like when you need to browse a guide for the game) or when exiting any movie. And really close to the end of the game you get like 6 movies, one after another, and it's way ahead of the teleport/save point you need to get there. This means there's a high chance of the game crashing at this point and you lose a LOT of progress.The patch, though, has a menu that can be used to skip this session completely (and other neat stuff/cheats as well).Since this is a game I'm really found ever since I played it for PSX, and the user patch fixes many of these compatibility problems, I am checking the ""recommend"" button. Just keep in mind you will still get some crashes from time to time as this is an old game and the patch is not perfect. If you can, you should prefer playing the PSX version."
