,Not Recommended,224920,33287846,Posted: 5 July,all,TheIronFistOfDeath,"TL;DR: Unless you're willing to search for hours only to have inconsistent loads, don't waste your money.I'm conflicted in my review.  The game is every bit as you remember it, be that good or bad.  You have 2 speeds: run and sprint, which often means falling off of small platforms.  The camera controls are some of the worst (no free control, only a quick snap to behind your character).  The story is as great as ever and the game does look better than it did in 1999 and the voice acting is still top notch.The problem, and the reason I can't recommend this game, is the problems getting it to even load.  The first time I got it to load, it took me 3 hours of trial and error.  The solution?  It loads perfectly once out of about 50 attempts.  No compatibility mode, no running as admin.  Just load, crash, load, crash, fiddle with settings, load, crash, load crash, default settings, load, crash, load, crash....(10 minutes later)..... load, works fine.  Seriously.  I managed to play it enough in 2 days to finish it but getting it to even start became a chore.Then there's the controller issues.  I used a wireless Xbox 360 controller (with the wireless receiver) and Pinnacle Game Profiler.  I recommend it.  Download the existing profile, then edit it.  The downloaded scheme is terrible.  Right trigger for attack, 2 buttons to devour souls, you get the idea.  I had one sound issue which forced me to restart the game (complete with several dozen crashes again), but otherwise it worked fine..... if you want to call it that.  If you're really jonesing for some nostalgia, watch a let's play on YouTube.  You'll save yourself a lot of frustration.The Good:+ Voice acting is still great+ Story holds upThe Bad:- Camera controls are still a messThe Ugly:-- Constant crashes at launch.Bottom line: this game performs like an abusive significant other.  It's crash, after crash, after crash, and just when you're ready to give up, it loads and works perfectly making you remember all the wonderful times you had when you first played it; making you think it's worked out its issues.  Then you try to start it again another time and it's right back to crashing and the cycle repeats.  Thankfully, it's a relatively short game."
