,Recommended,224920,14707227,"Posted: 1 March, 2015",all,Nacho,"It's a platforming classic. Can't go wrong with this game if you can handle it bit a little more than dated. Great puzzles, pretty good level design, amazing writing, fantastic atmosphere, and some of the best voice acting to ever show up in gaming. The ending is totally unsatisfying, but if you have the second game it should be all good."
76561198042479626,Recommended,224920,14601300,"Posted: 22 February, 2015",all,BrambleLamb,"I remember wanting this game as a kid, so I jumped at the chance to get it. Legacy of Kain: Soul Reaver is a great game. The agency, while it takes some time to become competent with due to poor but doable controls, feels really good. As you play you become better at playing, almost as if mirroring Razael's revival and strengthening. The game has a steady drip of interesting lore and a plot that leaves you wondering what the next part is. The puzzles often have you stumped until you remember that you can change the world by changing planes, which adds a layer of depth to them. The combat feels pretty decent but simple and can take a bit to become good as different enemies actually have slightly different approaches. The boss fights though are almost all amazing in that they are not blunt fighting but more puzzles. When you die you simply shift to the spectral plane, giving you a chance to come up with a new plan. The platforming, much like the typical combat, is simple. Unlike the combat though, gets more depth as you unlock more abilities.Obviously the game has its flaws: dated graphics, occasional crashes with no catalyst, poor controls, and the such. But those really do come with older games and are outweighed by the better aspects of this game. This game isn't long, but it certainly isn't short. If this game has caught your eye at all, I'd definitely recommend it."
