,Recommended,224920,26950152,"Posted: 23 November, 2016",all,C H R I S ラビオリ,"The year is 1999.The series was a reasonably established and when we found out there was going to be a new one, everyone was excited to see Kain's progression as a vampire and his expertly written narration of an exciting new story.And then the trailers were released. We are suddenly told that Kain is the antagonist of the game and that was truely puzzeling. It wasn't often that you saw the protagonist of the earlier games be the bad guy. But enough about/back in the day/stories. Let's talk about the game.THE STORY. Is it any good?The Legacy of Kain series has always had delicious, delicious narration throughout every game and this one is no different. It's a great way of giving exposition. Though sometimes they take control of your caracter for an unreasonable amount of time to vomit exposition down your throat, but at least it's all very well written.THE GAMEPLAY. Does it hold up?This game was well made and rarely bugged out and had great mechanics and decent camera control. (In egoraptor's voice: for the time...) The thing is about third person games, they didn't have a clear idea of how to most efficiently program the controls, like most games at the time. And even so the camera sometimes get distracted with a wall or some♥♥♥♥♥♥that doesn't matter, it didn't really bother all that much for the most part because fighting had a lock on system and the geometry was mostly simple. The only problem I encountered was in the plataforming segments. This game has a lot of that. and sometimes there were stupid time constraints (because of the many puzzles) on top of plataforming and my 8 y.o. self got extremely frustrated at times.Fighting is pretty basic... And dying is virtually impossible because when you die in the material world you go back to the spiritual world where only goofy dobby looking monsters are present most of the time and they're not really much of a threat. And regaining health is just a matter of holding one button and sucking every cotton candy ball floating around all over the place (AKA Souls). But given how the game is mostly plataforming and puzzles, that's not really an issue.-------CONCLUSION-------In conclusion I'd give this game asexy voice naration/10.The controls are decent for 1999 and vampires are pretty coolsers.This game was a big inspiration for the guys who made Darksiders 2, I'm pretty sure. Both games are narated, puzzle driven stories with the bad guy being the protagonist of the earlier game, so if you like Darksiders you should really try Soul Reaver, or any Legacy of Kain game. Also I'd like to point out that Square Enix are remaking this game so I'm looking foward to that.Kain Dies.Not really."
